The bug comes from the way the URL are encoded in PDE/Core.

See this method processExtension(IPluginExtension extension) in org.eclipse.pde.internal.core.JavadocLocationManager:

In the try/catch, the string buffer is initialized with file:/ which leads to an invalid url on Linux when the file path starts with a '/'.

Why not using the library method toURI().toURL() that will append the "file:" automatically.
I propose the following patch. The two lines with TODO need to be double-checked. I don't know when this case can occur.

attr = javadoc.getAttribute("archive"); //$NON-NLS-1$
boolean archive = attr == null ? false : "true".equals(attr.getValue()); //$NON-NLS-1$
IPath modelPath = new Path(extension.getModel().getInstallLocation());
File file = modelPath.toFile();
StringBuffer buffer = new StringBuffer();
if (file.exists() && file.isFile()) {
	try {
		buffer.append(file.toURI().toURL());
	} catch (MalformedURLException e1) {
		buffer.append(modelPath.toPortableString()); // TODO 
	}
	buffer.append("!/"); //$NON-NLS-1$
	archive = true;
} else {
	buffer.append("file:/"); //TODO 
	buffer.append(modelPath.toPortableString());
}
buffer.append(path);
processPlugins(archive ? "jar:" + buffer.toString() : buffer.toString(), javadoc.getChildren()); //$NON-NLS-1$

